    {
      "id": "26.11.2-determination",
      "type": "provision",
      "section": "26.11.2",
      "text": "To determine whether a building or other structure is rigid or flexible as defined in Section 26.2, the fundamental natural frequency, n1, shall be established using the structural properties and deformational characteristics of the resisting elements in a properly substantiated analysis. Low-rise buildings, as defined in Section 26.2, are considered rigid.",
