    {
      "id": "26.10.1-table-notes",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.10.1",
      "text": "ᵃ Use 0.70 in Chapter 28, Exposure B, when z < 30 ft (9.1 m).\nNotes:\n1. Velocity pressure exposure coefficient Kz may be determined from the following formula:\n\nFor z < 15 ft     Kz = 2.01(15/zg)²/ᵅ\nFor z < 4.6 m     Kz = 2.01(4.6/zg)²/ᵅ\nFor 15 ft (4.6 m) ≤ z ≤ zg     Kz = 2.01(z/zg)²/ᵅ\nFor z > zg ≤ 3,280 ft (1,000 m)     Kz = 2.01\n\n2. α and zg are tabulated in Table 26.11-1.\n3. Linear interpolation for intermediate values of height z is acceptable.\n4. Exposure categories are defined in Section 26.7.",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.7",
        "26.11-1"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "metadata": {
